TASK: Create a reusable OptimizedImage React component that serves WebP with JPG/PNG fallback.

CONTEXT: Verdant Goods Co. React SPA at /home/workspace/verdant-goods-store. Uses TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Vite build. Images are in /images/ directory. WebP versions will be generated alongside originals.

STEPS:
1. Create /home/workspace/verdant-goods-store/client/src/components/OptimizedImage.tsx:

```tsx
import React from 'react';

interface OptimizedImageProps {
  src: string;
  alt: string;
  width?: number;
  height?: number;
  className?: string;
  loading?: 'lazy' | 'eager';
  sizes?: string;
  priority?: boolean;
}

export function OptimizedImage({
  src,
  alt,
  width,
  height,
  className,
  loading = 'lazy',
  sizes,
  priority = false,
}: OptimizedImageProps) {
  // Derive WebP path from original path
  const ext = src.match(/\.(png|jpe?g)$/i)?.[0] || '';
  const basePath = src.replace(/\.(png|jpe?g)$/i, '');
  const webpSrc = `${basePath}.webp`;

  // Check if this is a product mockup (VGC_*.png) that has responsive sizes
  const isProductMockup = src.includes('VGC_') && src.endsWith('.png');

  const srcSet = isProductMockup
    ? `${basePath}-400w.webp 400w, ${basePath}-800w.webp 800w, ${basePath}.webp 1200w`
    : undefined;

  const defaultSizes = isProductMockup
    ? '(max-width: 640px) 400px, (max-width: 1024px) 800px, 1200px'
    : undefined;

  return (
    <picture>
      {isProductMockup && srcSet ? (
        <source
          type="image/webp"
          srcSet={srcSet}
          sizes={sizes || defaultSizes}
        />
      ) : (
        <source type="image/webp" srcSet={webpSrc} />
      )}
      <img
        src={src}
        alt={alt}
        width={width}
        height={height}
        className={className}
        loading={priority ? 'eager' : loading}
        sizes={isProductMockup ? (sizes || defaultSizes) : undefined}
      />
    </picture>
  );
}
```

2. Verify the file compiles (no syntax errors, proper TypeScript types)
3. Report: file created with explanation of the component API

IMPORTANT:
- The component must be a named export (not default) for tree-shaking
- Keep it simple - no external dependencies
- The fallback <img> always uses the original src (PNG/JPG)
- WebP source is derived by replacing the extension
- Product mockup PNGs have -400w.webp and -800w.webp responsive variants
- Other images (ingredient-*.jpg, hero-*.jpg, etc.) only have a single .webp variant
